    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given medium model risk level, regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing, and low analytical sensitivity to the unexercised parameter variations. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for its intended use in supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
